#! The 1st International Workshop on Information Heterogeneity and Fusion in Recommender Systems (RecSys 2010) was held in Barcelona, Spain, on the 26th of September 2010, under the frame of the 4th ACM Conference on Recommender Systems (RecSys 2010). HetRec workshop represented a meeting point for researchers and practitioners interested in addressing the challenges posed by information heterogeneity in recommender systems and studying information fusion in this context. The main objectives of this meeting were to identify the main challenges, suggest and discuss novel ideas for addressing these challenges, and propose a research agenda for future research at the domain. A total of twelve papers were presented at the workshop. There were six long papers, three short papers, and three posters. Sixteen submissions were received, and each of them was reviewed by two members of the Programme Committee.

